    • Method Detail

      • print

        public static Debug.PrintResult print(String toFile,
                      String msg)
        A bare-knuckle logging method. If your real logging system (log4j, java.util.logging, etc.) seems to be not behaving, and something somehow seems to have hijacked System.out, you can use this method to make sure log messages are written to a file in a location you know (because you specifify it yourself).
        Parameters:
        toFile - Full path to the file to write the log message to. The file will be created if it does not exist.
        msg - The message to write
        Returns:
        The result of the print operation
